The Network formally advertised, processed, and recruited PhD students in 2014 and 2015 to support capacity building in clinical trials methodology</gtr:piContribution><gtr:sector>Public</gtr:sector><gtr:start>2015-01-01</gtr:start></gtr:collaborationOutput><gtr:collaborationOutput><gtr:collaboratingOrganisation>Lancaster University</gtr:collaboratingOrganisation><gtr:country>United Kingdom of Great Britain &amp; Northern Ireland (UK)</gtr:country><gtr:description>N78 -Development of user-friendly web-based software for conducting Bayesian Phase I dose-escalation studies</gtr:description><gtr:id>96376BC4-BDEA-4EC3-804D-7F50C8AC976E</gtr:id><gtr:impact>outputs due 2017</gtr:impact><gtr:outcomeId>578f5e62cfa472.03192168-1</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:partnerContribution>Phase I dose-escalation studies are essential to determine the safe dosing range of a novel
