We therefore propose to hold a workshop on HEAPs for about 50 attendees in Bristol, with three key aims. First, we plan to review the limited number of currently available guidelines addressing aspects of HEAPs. We also intend to collate information about the current usage of HEAPs in terms of their structure, content and purpose. Finally, we aim to provide a forum in which health economists and other interested parties engaged in applied economic evaluations can open a dialogue on appropriate methods of standardisation with a view to creating guidance in future work.</gtr:partnerContribution><gtr:piContribution>Network funding provided. Coapplicants within the Network</gtr:piContribution><gtr:sector>Public</gtr:sector><gtr:start>2015-01-01</gtr:start></gtr:collaborationOutput><gtr:collaborationOutput><gtr:collaboratingOrganisation>Newcastle University</gtr:collaboratingOrganisation><gtr:country>United Kingdom of Great Britain &amp; Northern Ireland (UK)</gtr:country><gtr:description>R45: Establishing a database of statistical expertise to support clinical trial oversight committees and develop capacity</gtr:description><gtr:id>A5FD9C9C-69F0-458E-82A8-E5AA933A7103</gtr:id><gtr:impact>Expected outcome- development of a database</gtr:impact><gtr:outcomeId>53f1fa0d556211.17858901-3</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:partnerContribution>Research collaborators working on development of database</gtr:partnerContribution><gtr:piContribution>Network funded research project
